## Who The $7K Budget Suits Best

The $7K budget supports four distinct buyer profiles, each with a different optimal allocation:

**Profile 1 — The Size Maximizer:** Wants the largest diamond for the budget. Best choice: 1.25ct I-VS2 GIA Excellent + classic solitaire at ~$5,200. I color in white gold at 1.25ct is borderline — upgrade to H if possible.

**Profile 2 — The Quality Maximizer:** Wants the best possible quality in a 1ct stone. Best choice: 1ct E-VS1 GIA Excellent + classic solitaire at ~$6,100. Spending above F at 1ct is premium-grade overkill for most buyers.

**Profile 3 — The Balanced Buyer:** Wants the optimal diamond + ring combination. Best choice: 1ct G-VS2 GIA Excellent + six-prong solitaire or pave setting at ~$5,000–$5,500.

**Profile 4 — The Crossover Buyer:** Recognizes the $7K threshold and uses it correctly. Best choice: 1.25ct H-VS2 GIA Excellent + simple setting at ~$5,900–$6,400. The face-up size advantage over 1ct is immediately visible on the hand.

